The 1986 season of the Bhutanese [[A-Division (Bhutan)|A-Division]] was the inaugural season of top-flight football in Bhutan. 10 teams competed, and the first championship was won by [[Royal Bhutan Army F.C.|Royal Bhutan Army]].<ref name="RSSSF1986">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutan86.html|title=Bhutan 1986|last=Burns|first=Peter|last2=Makdissi|first2=Albert| date=31 July 2003| website=www.rsssf.com|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref>

