'''Association Sportive de Carrefour''' ({{IPA-fr|a.sɔ.sja.sjɔ̃ spɔrtɪv kaʁfuʁ}}; commonly referred to as '''AS Carrefour''' or '''ASCAR'''<ref>[http://haiti-reference.com/pages/plan/arts-et-culture/sigles_a-d/ Haiti-Référence – Sigles et Acronymes Utilisés en Haïti: A-D] {{fr}}</ref>) is a professional [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Carrefour, Haiti]]. The club was promoted to the highest division of [[Haitian Football Federation|Haitian football]] for the first time in 2002.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haiti02.html|title=Haiti 2002|website=www.rsssf.com|access-date=2018-03-13}}</ref> After 2011, Carrefour was relegated to Division 2,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haiti2011.html|title=Haiti 2011|website=www.rsssf.com|access-date=2018-03-13}}</ref> and again to Division 3 concluding the 2014 season.<ref name="RSSSF_14">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haiti2014.html|title=Haiti 2014|website=www.rsssf.com|access-date=2018-03-13}}</ref>
