{{Infobox venue | name = North Athletic Complex | nickname = | image = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania|PA]], United States | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1998 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Robert Morris Colonials]] | operator = [[Robert Morris Colonials]] | surface = Natural grass | scoreboard = | estimated_cost = | suites = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 500 | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Robert Morris Colonials]] [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|(NCAA)]] }}
The '''North Athletic Complex''' is a [[softball]] and [[soccer]] venue in [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]], United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rmucolonials.com/sports/2013/9/9/athletics_0909134129.aspx|title=North Athletic Complex|publisher=rmucolonials.com|accessdate=2018-02-03}}</ref> It is home to the [[Robert Morris Colonials]] softball and soccer teams of the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] [[Northeast Conference]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://softball.isport.com/softball-fields/us/pennsylvania/moon-township/robert-morris-university-the-north-athletic-complex-868449|title=Robert Morris University - North Athletic Complex|publisher=isport.com|accessdate=February 3, 2018}}</ref> The venue has a capacity of 500.
The student recreation and fitness center at the North Athletic Complex will host early season games for the [[Robert Morris Colonials men's basketball|Robert Morris men's basketball team]] until construction is completed on the [[UPMC Events Center]] in 2019.
